## Quality Gates (MANDATORY for code/build tasks)

You MUST run quality gate checks before considering any code/build task complete. This is enforced by the runtime — the task will not be moved to done/ unless gates pass.

**After finishing your code changes, run:**

```bash
bash {{ company_root }}/operations/scripts/pre-done-checks.sh /path/to/product/code/
```

This checks: build succeeds, linter passes (if configured), tests pass (if they exist), and build output exists (smoke check).

- If any gate FAILS: fix the issue and re-run
- If you cannot fix it: the task will be moved to failed/ with the gate results
- Do NOT skip this step — the runtime verifies independently

The quality gate script path is: `{{ company_root }}/operations/scripts/pre-done-checks.sh`
